## Key Takeaways for Families

**Start here:** Contact the **Utah Department of Health and Human Services Medicaid office** to apply. The search results do not provide a specific phone number or online portal URL; you'll need to call or visit the main DHHS website to locate the Medicaid application process.

**Three-tier system:** If your loved one's income is below 100% of the federal poverty level, they qualify for **QMB** (the most comprehensive—covers premiums, deductibles, and copayments). If income is between 100-120% FPL, they qualify for **SLMB** (Part B premiums only). If between 120-135% FPL, they may qualify for **QI** (Part B premiums only, but with no guaranteed funding).

**The critical gotcha:** The **QI program may close to new applicants** if Utah's annual federal allocation runs out. Before investing time in an application, call Medicaid to confirm QI is still accepting applicants for 2026.

**Timeline:** Expect up to 45 days for QMB approval, but SLMB and QI can be retroactive 3 months, meaning you could receive back-payment of premiums if approved.

**Asset limits matter:** You can have up to $9,950 in countable assets (individual) or $14,910 (couple), but your home and one vehicle don't count. Most families don't realize savings accounts and investments count toward this limit.

